Writing alpha=dim ker(iota_-), beta=dim ker(iota_+),
  c=dim(K_-/(K_- intersect K_+)), r=rank(mu_+),
the exact residual criterion is alpha+c<=beta+r.  Here it reads
  2+15<=1+27.
The additional optimal-section cover condition is c<=r, here 15<=27.
Both pass.  The ambient shortcut fails because dim ker(phi)=45>41-2.

The raw cut-boundary construction is valid but insufficient in this case.
Its natural-order rank is 6; the best of 49 tested target/fundamental order
placements has rank 12, and the union of all 49 images still has rank 12.
Thus vertex reordering does not recover the seven higher kernel directions.

